Objectives:
1. seeking support for an international, interdisciplinary workshop in Mauritius to initiate an integrated assessment of the country's natural resource use;
2. To identify resource conservation measures;
3. To prepare a long-term research andeducation program that involves members from Mauritius, other East African countries and the USA.

Objectives:
To obtain qualitative and quantitative information relating to neurological rehabilitation care needs in Mauritius.  The needs assessment will comprise a gap analysis and a priority-setting exercise which will cover the following:
-incidence/prevalence of stroke, spinal cord injury and traumatic brain injury;
-types of services and infrastructure available for patients in need of neurological rehabilitation;
-type of long term care provided to patients with severe neurological disease;
-human resources available in the country for provision of neurological rehabilitation;
-specific training programmes available in this area; and
-amenability of public infrastructure for persons with disabilities.

To act as a facilitator and to provide a platform for the main stakeholders in the Energy Sector to open up a dialogue on the promotion of Renewable Energy Sources/technologies for a cleaner and more energy secure Mauritius.
The aims of the project (workshop) were to:
1. identify the major players in the RE industry;
2. identify projects in the field of RE that could be funded by MRC;
3. identify the barriers to the establishment and growth of a RE industry; and
4. provide input to the Ministry of Public Utilities for the formulation of a RE Master Plan for the Republic of Mauritius.

Terms of Reference:
-to advise the MRC on the design of the semi-mobile/permanent science labs and suggest modifications, if necessary, based on the proposed drawings;
-to make recommendations to the MRC on the health and safety aspects of the semi-mobile/permanent science lab;
-to make recommendations to the MRC on the choice of materials to be used to refurbish the 20 x 8 container into a semi-mobile / permanent science lab and recommend the materials best suited for the local climate bearing in mind the cost effectiveness;
-to provide for the complete refurbishment of the container into a semi-mobile / permanent science lab prototype including the interior and exterior works;
-to provide an estimate on the costing for the complete refurbishment of the container into a semi-mobile / permanent science lab prototype.

Objectives of Project:
1. Analysis of the current status of sustainability in residential buildings;
2. Study of existing international standards which are locally relevant for sustainability in residential building designs;
3. Layout of a general framework (within the defined scope of the project) for sustainable residential building design, including key recommendations.
